[00:09.13]I walked through valleys I didn’t choose
[00:13.32]Shadowed days, bruised by truth
[00:17.51]My tears were prayers with no sound
[00:21.70]Faith on its knees, face to the ground
[00:25.89]I asked You why, I asked You when
[00:30.08]All I heard was silence again
[00:34.27]But You were near when I couldn’t feel
[00:38.46]You were working wounds I couldn’t heal
[00:42.65]You don’t waste the broken places
[00:46.84]You don’t turn away from pain
[00:51.03]You write redemption into suffering
[00:55.22]And call it by my name
[00:59.41]You trade mourning clothes for praise
[01:03.60]Breathe life into what was slain
[01:07.79]Out of ashes, You raise beauty
[01:11.98]Out of sorrow, You remain
[01:16.17]I learned endurance in the fire
[01:20.36]Hope was born when strength expired
[01:24.55]You counted every sleepless night
[01:28.74]Held my heart through every fight
[01:32.93]What the enemy meant for the grave
[01:37.12]You bent toward mercy, You bent toward grace
[01:41.31]I was weak, but You were strong
[01:45.50]You carried me when I couldn’t go on
[01:49.70]You don’t waste the broken places
[01:53.89]You don’t abandon those who fall
[01:58.08]You bind the wounds of the shattered soul
[02:02.27]You restore what fear stole
[02:06.46]You turn scars into testimony
[02:10.65]Chains into living proof
[02:14.84]Out of the suffering, You make a witness
[02:19.03]Out of the wounded, You speak truth
[02:23.22]Though I walk through the darkest valley
[02:27.41]I will not fear, You’re close to me
[02:31.60]Your rod, Your staff, they steady my breath
[02:35.79]You lead me through, not just to death
[02:39.98]But resurrection waits beyond the pain
[02:44.17]A living hope that bears my name
[02:48.36]Now I stand redeemed, not ashamed
[02:52.55]The old has passed, I’m not the same
[02:56.74]What tried to break me bowed to Christ
[03:00.93]By His wounds, I found new life
[03:05.12]If anyone is lost like I was then
[03:09.31]Let this be the truth I send
[03:13.50]Suffering shaped me—but salvation saved me
[03:17.69]And hope rose up in the end
[03:21.88]You were faithful in the fire
[03:26.07]You were faithful in the storm
[03:30.26]And I am living proof
[03:34.46]That You restore.
